quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  33,63,"People ask you ˹O Prophet˺ about the Hour. Say, “That knowledge is only with God. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near.”"
  33,64,"Surely God condemns the disbelievers, and has prepared for them a blazing Fire"
  33,65,to stay there for ever and ever—never will they find any protector or helper
  33,66,"On the Day their faces are ˹constantly˺ flipped in the Fire, they will cry, “Oh! If only we had obeyed God and obeyed the Messenger!”"
  33,67,"And they will say, “Our Lord! We obeyed our leaders and elite, but they led us astray from the ˹Right˺ Way"
  33,68,"Our Lord! Give them double ˹our˺ punishment, and condemn them tremendously.”"
  33,69,"O believers! Do not be like those who slandered Moses, but God cleared him of what they said. And he was honourable in the sight of God"
  33,70,"O believers! Be mindful of God, and say what is right"
  33,71,"He will bless your deeds for you, and forgive your sins. And whoever obeys God and His Messenger, has truly achieved a great triumph"
  33,72,"Indeed, We offered the trust to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, but they ˹all˺ declined to bear it, being fearful of it. But humanity assumed it, ˹for˺ they are truly wrongful ˹to themselves˺ and ignorant ˹of the consequences˺"
  33,73,"so that God will punish hypocrite men and women and polytheistic men and women, and God will turn in mercy to believing men and women. For God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"